    <persName>
        <forename>Joseph</forename>
        <surname>Paxton</surname>
    </persName>
    
    <note type="dates"><date>1803–65</date></note>
    <sex value="M"/>
    <note type="biography">
        <p>Gardener and architect. Gardener at the Horticultural Society gardens in Chiswick, 1823; foreman, 1824–6. Head gardener at Chatsworth, Derbyshire, 1826–50. Designed the layout of and constructions for the Great Exhibition in 1851. Superintended the re-erection of the Crystal Palace at Sydenham, 1853–4; director of the gardens there, 1854–65. Liberal MP for Coventry, 1854–65. Knighted, 1851.</p></note>
